quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,When the sky splits asunder
  84,2,"And responds to its Lord, and it is bound [to respond]"
  84,3,And when the earth is levelled
  84,4,"And it throws out its contents, and becomes void"
  84,5,"And responds to its Lord, and it is bound [to respond]"
  84,6,"O human! You do indeed have to put in hard labour to go to your Lord, and then you meet Him"
  84,7,And as for him whose book of deeds is placed in his right hand
  84,8,He will then face his accounting with ease
  84,9,And he will turn to his own people in joy
  84,10,And as for him whose book of deeds is given to him behind his back
  84,11,"He will pray for [his own death and] destruction"
  84,12,And he will burn in blazing Fire
  84,13,"He had indeed been living happily engrossed [on earth] among people of his own kind"
  84,14,"He had indeed thought he would never return [to life]"
  84,15,Yes indeed! His Lord had kept a watch over him
  84,16,"But no! [He shall not continue to remain dead.] I swear by the afterglow of sunset"
  84,17,"And by the night, and what it veils in its darkness"
  84,18,"And by the moon, at its full"
  84,19,"You [humans] do move from stage to stage"
  84,20,"Then how come they believe not [in a life to come]"
  84,21,"And when the Qur'aan is read out to them, they prostrate not"
  84,22,"On the contrary, they who suppress the truth dny it [this divine writ]"
  84,23,And Allah knows what they keep to themselves
  84,24,"So give them the prospect of grievous suffering [in the life to come]"
  84,25,But not to those who believe and do good deeds. For them is there a reward unending
  85,1,"By the sky, with its constellations of stars"
  85,2,"And by the Day [of Judgment] promised"
  85,3,"And witness [giving evidence in favour of or against anything on the Judgment Day] and those for or against whom the witness is giving evidence"
  85,4,Damned are the owners of the ditc
  85,5,Of the fuel-filled fire
  85,6,When they sat by it
  85,7,And witnessed what they did to the believers
  85,8,"And they took vengeance on them for nothing else but that they believed in Allah, the Omnipotent, the Embodiment of Praise"
  85,9,To Whom belongs the Absolute Sovereignty of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Witness to all things
  85,10,"Surely indeed, those who persecute believing men and believing women and repent not — for them will be the punishment of Hell, and for them the punishment by the Fire"
  85,11,"Surely indeed, those who believe and do good deeds — for them will be Gardens underneath which rivers flow. That is the Greatest Success"
  85,12,"Indeed, the Hold of your Lord is certainly severe"
  85,13,"It is He indeed Who does the original creation, and Who is capable of resurrecting His original creation when it is dead"
  85,14,"And He is the One Forgiving, Loving"
  85,15,Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,HE does what He wills
  85,17,Have you come to know the story of the armies
  85,18,Of Pharaoh and of (the ancient tribe of) Thamood
  85,19,"Yet, [despite knowing the story of how those ancient peoples were destroyed for their transgressions] those that suppress the Truth live in denial"
  85,20,And Allah surrounds them unawares
  85,21,"Nay, [non-believers' denial notwithstanding,] this is a glorious Qur'an"
  85,22,In a well-protected format
  86,1,By the sky and the Taariq
  86,2,— And what do you understand what the Taariq is
  86,3,It is the shining star —
  86,4,Not a soul but has a protector over it
  86,5,Let man then see how he is created
  86,6,"He is created by means of fluid [blood] spurting"
  86,7,Out from between the spine and the ribs
  86,8,"It [blood] is certainly indeed capable of its return"
  86,9,The Day secrets are disclosed
  86,10,"For him [man] there will then be no power, and no helper"
  86,11,"By the sky, ever returning [revolving]"
  86,12,And by the earth with its surface cracking open again and again with new growth of plants and vegetation
  86,13,"It [Qur'aan] is indeed a decisive Word"
  86,14,And it is not for just sport and amusement
  86,15,"They [suppressors of Truth] are indeed hatching a plot"
  86,16,"And I [Allah] am devising a plot"
  86,17,So let those who suppress the Truth go their way; let them go for a little while